Is it okay that I'm inside?

00:00:31.564 --> 00:00:33.332 line:0%
-Absolutely.
-Okay.

00:00:33.365 --> 00:00:35.601 line:0%
As we understand,
this place has some...

00:00:35.634 --> 00:00:37.703 line:0%
-very interesting history also.
-It does.

00:00:37.736 --> 00:00:41.607
Samuel Fern is the owner
that is really,

00:00:41.640 --> 00:00:44.410
um, credited
to building this property.

00:00:44.443 --> 00:00:46.412
-He had slaves, right?
-He did.

00:00:46.445 --> 00:00:48.915
There were three slaves
that were recorded.

00:00:48.948 --> 00:00:50.450
But it was recorded earlier

00:00:50.483 --> 00:00:53.286
-that he did actually have
four slaves, -Four slaves.

00:00:53.319 --> 00:00:55.455
-and, um...
-What happened to the other one?

00:00:55.488 --> 00:00:57.557
He... did... f...

00:00:57.590 --> 00:00:59.525
es-escape, I guess.

00:00:59.558 --> 00:01:02.829
-He actually...
he actually ran away. -Yay...!

00:01:02.862 --> 00:01:05.631
♪ ♪

00:01:05.664 --> 00:01:08.067
<i> Colleen gave us a tour
 of the land,</i>

00:01:08.100 --> 00:01:10.937
<i>and surprisingly, I didn't feel
 the urge to run away.</i>

00:01:10.970 --> 00:01:13.506
So, you want to know what
one of the most ironic things

00:01:13.539 --> 00:01:15.508
about where
we're standing right now?

00:01:15.541 --> 00:01:17.410
-That we're not working?
-(Sutton laughs)

00:01:17.443 --> 00:01:19.445
Is look how close we are
to the river.

00:01:19.478 --> 00:01:21.247
Kentucky was a slave state.

00:01:21.280 --> 00:01:23.883
That's Indiana--
and that was a free state.

00:01:23.916 --> 00:01:26.018
Wait a minute, wait a minute,
wait a minute, wait a minute.

00:01:26.051 --> 00:01:28.488
-You had a slave living
right here... -Yes, sir.

00:01:28.521 --> 00:01:30.957
-staring at freedom every day.
-Yes. Absolutely.

00:01:30.990 --> 00:01:32.959
-Wow. -That's how committed
black people are

00:01:32.992 --> 00:01:35.661
to not swimming, is that
we would rather stay slaves

00:01:35.694 --> 00:01:38.297
-than swim 50 yards to freedom.
-That is... Well, you know.

00:01:38.330 --> 00:01:40.733
<i> But that's not to say I
 didn't see anything suspicious</i>

00:01:40.766 --> 00:01:41.968
<i> on the property.</i>

00:01:42.001 --> 00:01:43.603
Hey, Colleen, what's that?

00:01:43.636 --> 00:01:46.172
YARD: It looks like a place
to hang black people.

00:01:46.205 --> 00:01:48.908
Uh, no. Actually, I think
it was more of a pulley system,

00:01:48.941 --> 00:01:50.776
where they were able
to bring heavy objects

00:01:50.809 --> 00:01:53.212
from down low up to
the third floor of the mansion.

00:01:53.245 --> 00:01:54.881
-Oh, like black people?
-Oh, I love that.

00:01:54.914 --> 00:01:56.315
No, not like black people.

00:01:56.348 --> 00:01:58.251
How authentic
can these weddings get?

00:01:58.284 --> 00:02:00.620
